ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.37                 Enzyme
NAME        epi-isozizaene synthase;
            SCO5222 protein
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase [(+)-epi-isozizaene-forming]
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = (+)-epi-isozizaene + diphosphate [RN:R07830]
ALL_REAC    R07830
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     (+)-epi-isozizaene [CPD:C16269];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Requires Mg2+ for activity. The displacement of the diphosphate group of farnesyl diphosphate occurs with retention of configuration [1]. In the soil-dwelling bacterium Streptomyces coelicolor A3(2), the product of this reaction is used by EC 1.14.13.106, epi-isozizaene 5-monooxygenase, to produce the sesquiterpene antibiotic albaflavenone [2].
